t\ngalaxies undergo faster structural evolution, consistent with previous results.\nInterestingly, star-forming galaxies' sizes and densities evolve at rates\nsimilar to those of quiescent galaxies. It is therefore possible that the same\nphysical processes drive the structural evolution of both populations,\nsuggesting that \"dry mergers\" may not be the sole culprit in this size\nevolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Jun 2009 15:25:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 6 Mar 2010 00:39:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 26 Mar 2010 02:42:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-03-29"}
