ay\nsources are most probably identified with CVs and AGN, as inferred from the\ncolours and flux ratios of their likely optical counterparts. Beyond the\nfinding of new thermally emitting INSs, our study aims at constraining the\nspace density of this Galactic population at great distances and at determining\nwhether their apparently high density is a local anomaly or not.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Jun 2009 15:16:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
